<subSubSection pageId="19" pageNumber="62" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="19.[111,649,1515,1700]" lastBlockId="19.[677,1210,216,370]" pageId="19" pageNumber="62">
This leaf, found associated with the stem of 
<figureCitation captionStart="FIG" captionStartId="15.[115,124,1635,1652]" captionTargetId="figure-29@16.[178,786,587,913]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIG. 9. — Silicified plants from the Permian of Sardinia: A, Cordaixylon sp., transverse section of a partly decorticated small stem with a solid parenchymatous pith; on the left the closely associated rachis (P) with several xylem bundles may represent a petiole of the same plant (SAR24B4L13);B, Cordaites leaves associated with Pecopteris pinnules;the broadest leaf (CC) with interfascicular scleren-" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4607883" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4607883/files/figure.png" pageId="19" pageNumber="62">Figure 9A</figureCitation>
, has a thin lamina (
<quantity box="[423,519,1546,1573]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="19" pageNumber="62" unit="mm" value="0.4">0.4 mm</quantity>
), a smooth surface and very closely spaced veins (less than 
<quantity box="[115,199,1610,1637]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="19" pageNumber="62" unit="mm" value="0.4">0.4 mm</quantity>
interval, i.e. about 25 per cm). Rectangular sclerotic strands extend above and below veins; the mesophyll is differentiated into palisade and more or less spongy tissues. Despite similarities with the species 
<taxonomicName box="[758,893,247,274]" class="Pinopsida" family="Cordaitaceae" genus="Cordaites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cordaitales" pageId="19" pageNumber="62" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lingulatus">
<emphasis box="[758,893,247,274]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="62">C. lingulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Grand’Eury as illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation author="RENAULT B." box="[677,843,279,306]" pageId="19" pageNumber="62" pagination="213 - 348" refId="ref13831" refString="RENAULT B. 1879. - Structure comparee de quelques tiges de la flore Carbonifere, Nouvelles Archives du Museum d'Histoire Naturelle 2: 213 - 348." type="journal article" year="1879">Renault (1879)</bibRefCitation>
this leaf may represent variability of other species like 
<taxonomicName authority="Germar" authorityName="Germar" box="[899,1205,311,338]" class="Pinopsida" family="Cordaitaceae" genus="Cordaites" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cordaitales" pageId="19" pageNumber="62" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="principalis">
<emphasis box="[899,1112,311,337]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="62">Cordaites principalis</emphasis>
Germar
</taxonomicName>
, as illustrated by 
<bibRefCitation author="HARMS V. L. &amp; LEISMAN G. A." box="[852,1138,343,370]" pageId="19" pageNumber="62" pagination="1041 - 1064" refId="ref13118" refString="HARMS V. L. &amp; LEISMAN G. A. 1961. - The anatomy and morphology of certain Cordaites leaves. Journal of Paleontology 35: 1041 - 1064." type="journal article" year="1961">Harms &amp; Leisman (1961)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
